                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180401-26-victim209 t18180401-26-viclabel150"></join>. On the 19th of March, about eleven o'clock in the day, I was by the New Church, in the <placeName id="t18180401-26-crimeloc151">Strand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180401-26-crimeloc151" type="placeName" value="Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180401-26-crimeloc151" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180401-26-off148 t18180401-26-crimeloc151"></join>, and felt my pocket move, I turned round, and saw my handkerchief in the prisoner's hand - I seized him, took it from him, and charged him with picking my pocket; he said poverty had induced him to do it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180401-26-person211">
                  JOHN 
                  STOCKDALE
               <interp inst="t18180401-26-person211" type="surname" value="STOCKDALE"></interp>
